reviews.review_text: Building Towards April Thanks for the up grade Bill. Uneven sound doesn't prevent my ole ears from enjoying this night at the Fillmore. Sounds like a matrix. 1st SF show sans Mickey? Boys developing the chug a lug sound that would turn up on Skull and Roses in all its power and glory. Love hearing the crowd response to Pig coming out for Hard To Handle. Also enjoy this era's echoes of Jerry's sound and approach that we hear on David Crosby's If Only I Could Remember My Name.

Nice Little Show! Sound isn't terrific and the boys are a little off key at times, but a good glimpse of what would be the amazing summer of '71 Dead.  Great organ on Loser, too.  Pig was definitely better on the B3 than he got got credit for.
